'''Ōtomo no Sukunamaro''' (大伴 宿奈麻呂) was a {{ill|noble|ja|貴族|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|waka poet|ja|歌人|12=draft|12=draft}} of the early {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|12=draft|12=draft}}. He was the third son of {{ill|Ōtomo no Yasumaro|ja|大伴安麻呂|12=draft|12=draft}}. His court Rank was {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|12=draft|12=draft}}, and he served as {{ill|Benkan|ja|弁官|12=draft|12=draft}} (Right Major Controller).

== Career ==
In the {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|12=draft|12=draft}} era under {{ill|Empress Genmei|ja|元明天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, Sukunamaro was promoted three Ranks from {{ill|Jurokui|ja|従六位上|1=Junior Sixth Rank|lt=Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Jugo-i|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in 708 CE. Over the next years, his career progressed steadily:
- Promoted to {{ill|Jugo-i no Jō|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in 712 CE.
- Advanced to {{ill|Shogo-i|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in 717 CE and to {{ill|Shogo-i no Jō|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|12=draft|12=draft}} in 720 CE under {{ill|Empress Genshō|ja|元正天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}.

While serving as Governor of {{ill|Bizen Province|ja|備前国|12=draft|12=draft}} in 719 CE, he was concurrently appointed Inspector of {{ill|Aki Province|ja|安芸国|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Suo Province|ja|周防国|12=draft|12=draft}}. 

In the first year of {{ill|Shinki|ja|神亀|12=draft|12=draft}} (724 CE), shortly after {{ill|Emperor Shōmu|ja|聖武天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} ascended the throne, he was promoted to {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|12=draft|12=draft}}. He is believed to have passed away around 727 CE.

Sukunamaro's poetry includes love songs addressed to a court lady, with two of his poems preserved in the {{ill|Man'yōshū|ja|万葉集|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=4|poems=532, 533}}</ref> According to a later entry in the same collection, he resided in Tamura-ri (modern-day {{ill|Nara City|ja|奈良市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Nitatsujichō) and held the post of Right Major Controller.<ref>{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=4|poem=759}}</ref>

