'''Ōtomo no Sukunamaro''' (大伴 宿奈麻呂) was a {{ill|noble|ja|貴族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/noble|qq=}} and {{ill|waka poet|ja|歌人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/waka poet|qq=}} of the early {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara period|qq=}}. He was the third son of {{ill|Otomo no Otomaro|ja|大伴安麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo no Yasumaro|qq=}}. His court Rank was {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jushi-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}}, and he served as {{ill|Benkan|ja|弁官|1=Benkan (administrator)|lt=Benkan|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Benkan|qq=}} (Right Major Controller).

== Career ==
In the {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wadō|qq=}} era under {{ill|Empress Genmei|ja|元明天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Genmei|qq=}}, Sukunamaro was promoted three Ranks from {{ill|Jurokui|ja|従六位上|1=Junior Sixth Rank|lt=Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jurokui|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|qq=}} to {{ill|Jugo-i|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugo-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in 708 CE. Over the next years, his career progressed steadily:
- Promoted to {{ill|Jugo-i no Jō|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugo-i no Jō|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in 712 CE.
- Advanced to {{ill|Shogo-i|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogo-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in 717 CE and to {{ill|Shogo-i no Jō|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogo-i no Jō|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in 720 CE under {{ill|Empress Genshō|ja|元正天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Genshō|qq=}}.

While serving as Governor of {{ill|Bizen Province|ja|備前国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bizen Province|qq=}} in 719 CE, he was concurrently appointed Inspector of {{ill|Aki Province|ja|安芸国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aki Province|qq=}} and {{ill|Suo Province|ja|周防国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suo Province|qq=}}. 

In the first year of {{ill|Shinki|ja|神亀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinki|qq=}} (724 CE), shortly after {{ill|Emperor Shōmu|ja|聖武天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Shōmu|qq=}} ascended the throne, he was promoted to {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jushi-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}}. He is believed to have passed away around 727 CE.

Sukunamaro's poetry includes love songs addressed to a court lady, with two of his poems preserved in the {{ill|Man'yōshū|ja|万葉集|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Man'yōshū|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=4|poems=532, 533}}</ref> According to a later entry in the same collection, he resided in Tamura-ri (modern-day {{ill|Nara City|ja|奈良市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara City|qq=}}, Nitatsujichō) and held the post of Right Major Controller.<ref>{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=4|poem=759}}</ref>

